Court will set the matter for preliminary hearing. States request on bail: $1500 cash bond no contact with victims 1 or 2. Defendant is currently out on a $750 cash bond on 21CF381. In that file he showed up late in October of last year. He failed to appear in November of last year. Atty Craker argues against the cash as requested by the State. Atty Craker represents the defendant on the older file. Defendant has been in good contact wtih Atty Craker. Defendant was taking things seriously. He did show up late but did show up later that morning as he was having car troubles. Defendant did turn himself in the very next day voluntarily. No recent criminal history. Family in Duluth. Does have ties to the Duluth, MN area. Defendant is homeless and spending a lot of time in the homeless encampments. Defendant does not have any cash he can post at this time.
Court reviews allegations in the older file and reviewing allegations in the new file. The allegations are concerning to the Court. There is significant history of domestic abuse towards hospital staff which were unprevoked. Court also indicates that Defendant's address is general delivery.
